'''Elite Answers Inc.''', formerly named Eliteweb, is a [[Toronto]]-based company that provides corporations and organisations with [[email marketing]], [[web site]] development, [[search engine optimization]] and corporate [[social networking]] tools. Elite Answers began operations with the launch of the Eliteweb.cc search engine on October 11, 2005;<ref>[http://www.itbusiness.ca/it/client/en/home/News.asp?id=37040 “Canadian startup takes on search engine giants,” IT Business Canada, October 11, 2005]</ref><ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/RTGAM.20051011.gteliteweb1011/BNStory/Technology “Eliteweb.cc Goes Live,” Toronto Globe & Mail, October 11, 2005]</ref> the search engine was later renamed EliteAnswers.com. In 2006, the company expanded its offerings to include Elite Email, an e-mail marketing program for small businesses, and other Net-based services.<ref>[http://www.dmnews.com/Elite-Email-Debuts-E-mail-Marketing-Program-for-Small-Businesses/article/91386/ “Elite Email Debuts E-mail Marketing Program for Small Businesses,” DM News, May 31, 2006]</ref> In 2007, the company was named one of Canada's Top 20 Up and Comers by the Branham Group and Backbone Magazine.<ref>[http://www.backbonemag.com/Magazine/Top_20_Up_and_Comers.asp “Top 20 Up and Comers,” Backbone Magazine, May 2007]</ref> In 2009, Elite Email was rated one of the top 50 Email Service Providers by Website Magazine.<ref>[http://www.websitemagazine.com/content/blogs/posts/pages/targeted-smarter-advertising-for-web-pros-september-2009.aspx “Top 50: E-mail Service Providers,” Website Magazine, September 2009]</ref>

President, Robert Burko, made front-page news in the ''[[Toronto Star]]'' in a heartfelt story titled "A heart attack, a wedding and an iPad" where technology was used to save a wedding day after the father of the bride suffered a heart-attack 48 hours before the wedding.<ref>[https://www.thestar.com/news/article/1003638--a-heart-attack-a-wedding-and-an-ipad “A heart attack, a wedding and an iPad,” Toronto Star, June 7, 2011]</ref>

